I have successfully implemented the remaining CRUD logic in `app/main.py`.

Here is a summary of the changes made:
1. **Model Adjustment**: I added a `TodoCreate` Pydantic model in `app/models.py` to handle `POST` and `PUT` request bodies, ensuring the `id` field isn't required when creating or updating items.
2. **`POST /todos`**: Implemented the creation of a new item with auto-incrementing ID logic, responding with a `201 Created` status code and the created item.
3. **`PUT /todos/{todo_id}`**: Implemented updating the `title` and `completed` status of an existing item. If the item doesn't exist, it correctly raises a `404 Not Found` error.
4. **`DELETE /todos/{todo_id}`**: Implemented deletion functionality using list pop, responding with a `204 No Content` status code. If the item isn't found, it raises a `404 Not Found`.

I also ran a quick test script to verify all endpoints are functioning properly and handling not-found constraints effectively. The modern Todo API is fully functional now!
